        "# FLUX.2 Klein 9B Models\n\nChoose **one** diffusion model based on your GPU and use case.\n\nHugging Face access required\n\nThe FLUX.2 Klein 9B diffusion models are gated.\n\nSign in to Hugging Face, open the model page, and click Agree and access repository before downloading.\n\nDirect download links will not work until access has been accepted.\n\n## 1. Diffusion model\n\nPlace your chosen model in:\n\n`ComfyUI/models/diffusion_models/`\n\n**FP8**  \nBest general choice for most modern NVIDIA GPUs.\n\n[flux-2-klein-9b-fp8.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.2-klein-9b-fp8/resolve/main/flux-2-klein-9b-fp8.safetensors)\n\n**Full BF16**  \nHighest precision version, but uses the most VRAM.\n\n[flux-2-klein-9b.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.2-klein-9B/resolve/main/flux-2-klein-9b.safetensors)\n\n**NVFP4**  \nBest choice for NVIDIA Blackwell GPUs such as RTX 50 series.\n\n[flux-2-klein-9b-nvfp4.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.2-klein-9b-nvfp4/resolve/main/flux-2-klein-9b-nvfp4.safetensors)\n\n**KV FP8**  \nBest for image editing and workflows that reuse reference images.  \nUse this with the **FluxKVCache** node in newer ComfyUI versions.\n\n[flux-2-klein-9b-kv-fp8.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.2-klein-9b-kv-fp8/resolve/main/flux-2-klein-9b-kv-fp8.safetensors)\n\n## 2. Text encoder\n\nPlace in:\n\n`ComfyUI/models/text_encoders/`\n\n[qwen_3_8b_fp8mixed.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/flux2-klein-9B/resolve/main/split_files/text_encoders/qwen_3_8b_fp8mixed.safetensors)\n\n## 3. VAE\n\nPlace in:\n\n`ComfyUI/models/vae/`\n\n[flux2-vae.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/flux2-dev/resolve/main/split_files/vae/flux2-vae.safetensors)\n\n## 4. Folder structure\n\n```text\nComfyUI/\n└── models/\n    ├── diffusion_models/\n    │   └── one FLUX.2 Klein 9B model here\n    ├── text_encoders/\n    │   └── qwen_3_8b_fp8mixed.safetensors\n    └── vae/\n        └── flux2-vae.safetensors"
      ],
      "color": "#222",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    },
